This example shows how to integrate Zend Framework 1.11 application with Doctrine 1.2.

INSTALLATION

* Download or symlink library/Zend from Zend Framework 1.11 package (http://zendframework.com/download/latest) to library/ folder
* Download or symlink lib/Doctrine from Doctrine 1.2 package (https://github.com/doctrine/doctrine1) to library/ folder
* Edit application/configs/application.ini and alter doctrine.dsn entry:

doctrine.dsn = "mysql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DATABASE_NAME" 

* Check if installation works:

cd PROJECT_DIRECTORY
php ./scripts/doctrine-cli.php
